cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about building neural machine translation systems using synthetic parallel data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence and deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also presents experiments and results, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning), which deals with machine learning and statistical learning theory. Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the use of synthetic data for machine translation.
